text: Department of the Treasury Internal Revenue Service
This obsoletes IRM 2.13.21, Enterprise Networks, Telecommunications Encryption Standards.
″ The material in IRM 2.13.21 is obsolete because a commercial vendor provides encryption on all ″ data links as part of TNET WAN managed service.

This IRM is to be used by the Information Technology (IT) organization and other Business Operating Divisions needing telecommunications encryption services. It pertains to all IRS telecommunications staff responsible for installing, operating, or maintaining encrypted data telecommunications links for the or transmittal of sensitive but unclassified data. This IRM is not applicable to the processing or transmittal of classified data.
